# Utility-Bar Icon Buttons and Dropdown Panels

## Icon button shape (L2 — 28 px ring)

All utility-bar icon triggers — left rail (apps, policy) and right rail — use the **L2 ring class**:

```tsx
import { APP_SHELL_UTILITY_L2_ICON_CLASS } from "./utility-bar.client"

// ✅ icon button (no dropdown)
<button type="button" aria-label={ariaLabel} className={cn(APP_SHELL_UTILITY_L2_ICON_CLASS, className)}>
  <BarIcon><Grip strokeWidth={2} /></BarIcon>
</button>

// ✅ icon button that opens a dropdown
<DropdownMenuTrigger asChild>
  <button
    type="button"
    aria-label={ariaLabel}
    className={cn(
      APP_SHELL_UTILITY_L2_ICON_CLASS,
      "data-[state=open]:bg-muted/55 data-[state=open]:text-foreground",
      className
    )}
  >
    <BarIcon><Grip strokeWidth={2} /></BarIcon>
  </button>
</DropdownMenuTrigger>
```

**`APP_SHELL_UTILITY_DISC_CLASS` (33 px, no ring) is for image-based discs only** — `AppShellBrandDisc` and `AppShellAvatarDisc`. Never use it for Lucide icon triggers.

Open-state: always `data-[state=open]:` — never `aria-expanded:`.

## Tooltip + dropdown trigger composition

```tsx
// ✅ correct nesting — Tooltip wraps both trigger and content
<DropdownMenu>
  <Tooltip>
    <TooltipTrigger asChild>
      <DropdownMenuTrigger asChild>
        <button ...>{icon}</button>
      </DropdownMenuTrigger>
    </TooltipTrigger>
    <TooltipContent side="bottom" align="center" sideOffset={8}>
      {tooltip}
    </TooltipContent>
  </Tooltip>
  <DropdownMenuContent ...>…</DropdownMenuContent>
</DropdownMenu>

// ❌ never use Menubar for a single-trigger apps launcher
<Menubar><MenubarMenu><MenubarTrigger>…</MenubarTrigger></MenubarMenu></Menubar>
```

## Dropdown panel chrome (matches AppShellUtilityDropdown)

```tsx
import { uiRadius, uiSurfaceElevation, uiTracking } from "#lib/design-system"

<DropdownMenuContent
  align="start"
  sideOffset={8}
  className={cn(
    "flex max-h-[min(92vh,40rem)] w-[min(20rem,calc(100vw-2rem))] min-w-0 flex-col overflow-hidden gap-0 p-0",
    "border border-border bg-card/95 text-card-foreground backdrop-blur-sm",
    uiRadius.popover,        // "rounded-xl"
    uiSurfaceElevation.raised, // "shadow-elevation-2"
    "ring-0 ring-offset-0",
  )}
>
  {/* Header strip — always present */}
  <div className="shrink-0 border-b border-border/50 px-4 py-3">
    <p className="text-xs font-semibold tracking-tight text-card-foreground">{title}</p>
    {subtitle ? (
      <p className={cn("mt-1 text-[11px] leading-snug text-muted-foreground", uiTracking.control)}>
        {subtitle}
      </p>
    ) : null}
  </div>

  {/* Scrollable body */}
  <div className="min-h-0 flex-1 overflow-y-auto overflow-x-hidden px-1.5 py-2">
    {children}
  </div>
</DropdownMenuContent>
```

Raw `MenubarContent`, `w-56`, or unstyled `DropdownMenuContent` are not acceptable — use the pattern above.

## Circular import note

`utility-dropdown.client.tsx` imports `APP_SHELL_UTILITY_L2_ICON_CLASS` from `utility-bar.client.tsx`.
Do **not** import `AppShellUtilityDropdown` back into `utility-bar.client.tsx` — inline the chrome instead.
